<item>
            <title>[JDK-8307466] java.time.Instant calculation bug in until and between methods</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8307466</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>Consider the following code:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;var t1 = Instant.parse(&amp;quot;2023-05-03T10:00:00.000999Z&amp;quot;);&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;var t2 = Instant.parse(&amp;quot;2023-05-03T10:00:01.000Z&amp;quot;);&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;var t3 = Instant.parse(&amp;quot;2023-05-03T10:00:01.001Z&amp;quot;);&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;System.out.println(MILLIS.between(t1, t2));&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;System.out.println(MILLIS.between(t1, t3));&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;br/&gt;
This prints:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;1000&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;1000&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;br/&gt;
Given that t3 is exactly one millisecond later than t2, it does not seem reasonable that they can both be 1000 milliseconds later than t1.&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;br/&gt;
The JavaDoc for between() states &amp;quot;The calculation returns a whole number, representing the number of complete units between the two temporals.&amp;quot;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;br/&gt;
Assuming I have understood this correctly, I think MILLIS.between(t1, t3) is correct but MILLIS.between(t1, t2) should return 999.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Reported to core-libs-dev mai:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://mail.openjdk.org/pipermail/core-libs-dev/2023-May/105229.html&quot;&gt;https://mail.openjdk.org/pipermail/core-libs-dev/2023-May/105229.html&lt;/a&gt;</description>
